ZH: 我昨天晚上在跑步时抽筋了。
EN: I got a muscle cramp while running last night.

ZH: 她经常在办公室抽筋。
EN: She often gets muscle cramps in the office.

ZH: 如果你抽筋了，伸直腿然后慢慢按摩可以缓解。
EN: If you get a muscle cramp, straighten your leg and gently massage it to alleviate the pain.

ZH: 老人容易抽筋，所以要多注意休息和运动。
EN: Older people are prone to muscle cramps, so they should pay more attention to rest and exercise.

ZH: 运动前做热身可以减少抽筋的几率。
EN: Doing warm-up exercises before sports can reduce the likelihood of getting muscle cramps.

ZH: 长时间坐在同一个姿势下容易抽筋。
EN: Sitting in the same position for a long time can easily lead to muscle cramps.

ZH: 长时间的剧烈运动可能会导致抽筋。
EN: Prolonged and intense exercise can lead to muscle cramps.

ZH: 他在游泳时腿抽筋，不得不停下来。
EN: He got a leg cramp while swimming and had to stop.

ZH: 抽筋可能是身体缺乏某种微量元素的表现。
EN: Muscle cramps can be a sign of the body lacking certain trace elements.

ZH: 躺着的时候抽筋特别疼。
EN: Muscle cramps are particularly painful when lying down.

ZH: 过度疲劳容易导致抽筋。
EN: Excessive fatigue can lead to muscle cramps.

ZH: 受伤的肌肉容易抽筋。
EN: Injured muscles are prone to cramps.

ZH: 随着年龄增长，抽筋的频率也会增加。
EN: As you get older, the frequency of muscle cramps also increases.

ZH: 如果你抽筋时感觉肌肉绷紧，可以尝试轻轻拉伸。
EN: If you feel muscle tension when you get a cramp, you can try gently stretching it.

ZH: 抽筋会影响到日常生活和运动。
EN: Muscle cramps can affect daily life and exercise.

ZH: 缺乏锻炼容易导致肌肉抽筋。
EN: Lack of exercise can easily lead to muscle cramps.

ZH: 抽筋可以是肌肉在过度紧张时的反应。
EN: Muscle cramps can be a reaction to excessive muscle tension.

ZH: 吃含钙丰富的食物可以减少抽筋的风险。
EN: Eating foods rich in calcium can reduce the risk of muscle cramps.

ZH: 在充分休息和睡眠的情况下，可以减少抽筋的发生。
EN: Adequate rest and sleep can reduce the occurrence of muscle cramps.
